reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Outstanding kit bag for men or women
reviews.reviewText: I use this kind of bag for travel. I have been searching for a new kit bag to replace one that I have used for many years. After some trial-and-error, I finally found the Zeemo bag and I am THRILLED. It is exactly what I needed. Unlike others, it holds its shape and looks good even when stuffed with items, despite being extremely lightweight. The organization is great - many pockets and water-resistant areas, but also a large, central interior. The new-to-me feature of the double zipper top is great. I wanted the bag to be able to hold a few items that would not fit in my older bag, and it does that easily (one is a full-size can of hairspray because the brand I use does not come in a travel size). Depending on how I pack it, it is able to partially collapse within the suitcase to save space. Finally, it is extremely well-made. This bag is advertised for men, but of course there is no gender distinction needed, and in fact I am a woman.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Classic Style That Will Appeal To Men Of All Ages
reviews.reviewText: A great investment for any man who wants to have his toiletries organized and easily accessible. The bag is stylish, durable, and easy to clean, making it perfect for frequent travelers. The bag is made from high-quality materials that are water-resistant and easy to clean. This is especially important for anyone who uses a lot of products, such as shampoos, conditioners, and body washes.The bag features multiple compartments, which makes it easy to organize different items. The main compartment is large enough to hold all of the basic toiletries, such as soap, a razor, and toothpaste. Additionally, there are several smaller zippered pockets for items like a toothbrush, floss, and small bottles of shampoo and other liquids. The bag also has an external zippered pocket, which is perfect for items that you want to have quick access to. This pocket is perfect for items like a comb, a hairbrush, or a small bottle of cologne.The Toiletry Bag for Men is designed to be durable as well. It has a sturdy zipper that is designed to hold up over time. The bag is also constructed from a material that is resistant to wear and tear, so it should last for many years with proper care. The water-resistant feature is another great benefit, as it keeps the contents of the bag dry in humid or wet environments.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Nice Bag - Time Will Tell
reviews.reviewText: I wanted to replace my existing toiletry bag that I have had for *30* years! No lie. It is nothing fancy - canvas exterior, zippered main area opened like a suitcase and no organization except for a decent-sized zippered pouch. It holds all my essentials well and is a good quality piece. What makes it special for me is it is fully lined in water-proof vinyl.I searched for weeks for a replacement. Low-priced, high-priced, hanging, countertop. I was about to pull the trigger and get one of those expensive bags from a high-end luggage maker and this ZEEMO 8L was suggested.What I like is the capacity to hold all my stuff and the main compartment is fully lined in vinyl with mesh pockets. There are so many places to properly store my toiletries and I’m in very satisfied with this bag.Now because I cannot just dump everything in it like my former bag, I have to find the right place for it all.The materials seem sturdy and the workmanship seems above average. I hope all the zippers and stitching last. One thing I did was round off the sharp crimped edges of all my tubes. This should minimize the possibility of cutting the vinyl or tearing the mesh.There is something that I would have done differently from a design perspective - the handle. It should be on the opposite side and the zipper magnetic closure should too (the possibility to TSA cable-lock the bag exists). If the bag is not tightly packed and you carry it by the handle, things in the pockets will fall from their location. Not much of an issue for me though.So in all, this seems like a great bag at a great price. Time will tell if it lasts for 30 years!
